Lower face excavated, concave; vertex impressed with a few fine punctures. Antennae more than half the length of the body, filiform, very slightly attenuated at the base and apex; joints cylindrical, the second half the length of the basal one, the third as long again as the second. Thorax twice as broad as long at the base; sides very oblique, quickly converging from base to apeX, straight behind the middle, slightly rounded anteriorly, apical angle produced, subacute‚ the hasal one very acute; basal margin broadly concave, emarginate on either side, its medial portion very obtusely rounded and slightly reflexed; upper surface smooth and shining, remotely impressed with very fine punctureS, only visible under a strong lens; medial disc covered with a broad black vitta, which extends from base to apex3 surface between this discoidal vitta and the lateral margin excavated, the lateral margin itself reflexed.
